intro: Eutassa biramulata, commonly known as the two-branched eutassa, is a flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its compound leaves and clusters of small white flowers. The plant typically grows in moist, shaded environments, such as tropical forests. Its roots are sometimes used in traditional medicine for their purported health benefits. The species is relatively rare and faces threats from habitat loss and overharvesting.
